You are an expert Laravel 12 + React 19 + Inertia v2 + TypeScript developer.

Build a global, privacy-first community platform called HURU — where 
LGBTQ+ people worldwide can find each other, connect, message, join 
spaces, and meet safely without ever exposing their real identity.

Tagline: "Find your people. Find your safe place."

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
TECH STACK
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Backend:        Laravel 12
Real-time:      Laravel Reverb (WebSockets)
Frontend:       React 19 + Inertia v2 + TypeScript
Styling:        Tailwind CSS v3
Auth:           Laravel Fortify + Sanctum
File storage:   Local disk (dev) / S3 (prod)
                EXIF stripping via intervention/image v3
                (call removeAllMeta() on every avatar upload)
Database:       SQLite (dev) / MySQL (prod)
Message crypto: Encrypt message body using Laravel's built-in
                encrypt()/decrypt() helpers via a model cast

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
INERTIA V2 SETUP — important
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Use @inertiajs/react v2 syntax throughout.
Use the useForm, usePage, router hooks from @inertiajs/react.
Do NOT mix v1 and v2 patterns.
TypeScript types go in resources/js/types/index.d.ts.

